I tweeted about this yesterday and quite a few people were surprised, so it's a good idea to repeat it.
</p>
<p>
<strong>If you run an ecommerce site on shared hosting, you can never be PCI compliant</strong> (because you're sharing the server with other code, other users, you're probably using FTP, etc).
</p>
<p>
Which ecommerce sites need to be PCI compliant? All of them.
</p>
